The Telegraph - Calcutta : Metro
 Friday, January 23, 2004  The City Diary
																																																																																		Calcutta Police on Thursday announced restrictions on using loudspeakers during Saraswati puja on January 26. Officials said puja organisers would have to take prior permission from the authorities for using loudspeakers. On January 26, loudspeakers would be allowed only inside the pandals from 7 am to 11 am and 6 pm to 9 pm. On January 27, the day of immersion, loudpeakers would be allowed from 7 am to 11 am only. They said microphones would not be allowed in silence zones. Guidelines of the high court and the pollution control board will also have to be followed.																																																		A division bench of Calcutta High Court on Thursday granted the anticipatory bail prayers of Shibaprosad Das, regional manager, Manish Kothari, assistant manager (collection) and Suman Deb, law officer of Standard Chartered Bank who were apprehending arrests in connection with a case of forcefully lifting a car owned by a lawyer, Om Jhunjhunwala, for alleged non-payment of loan instalments. Jhunjhunwala had filed a writ petition before Calcutta High Court alleging that even after repayment of loans, bank officials forcefully took possession of his Maruti car by engaging goons. Justice Barin Ghosh held that the police had done nothing to return the car to its owner after taking possession of the vehicle from the bank. Appearing for the bank, advocate Joymalya Bagchi claimed that his client was yet to receive Rs 1.47 lakh from Jhunjhunwala.																																																		Power supply to Burrabazar and Jorasanko is likely to be affected on Saturday as CESC will carry out maintenance work on its six KV switch board at Strand North Distribution station. As a result, a CESC spokesperson said, power supply to consumers in Burrabazar, Clive Row, Netaji Subhas Road, Ahiritola, Maharshi Debendra Row, Kashi Dutta Street, Nather Bagan, Kali Krishna Tagore Street, Nawab Lane, Canning Street, Jamunalal Bazaz Street, Nimtala Ghat Road, Strand Bank Road, PK Tagore Street, Jorasanko, Bechu Dutta Street, Cornwallis Street and BK Pal Avenue will be affected from 8.30 am to 10.30 am.																																																		A man was arrested for murder on Thursday. Sadek is the main accused in the murder of Nechar Ali, brutally killed following a dispute over money eight months ago. Sadik was picked up from Jora Biswaspara area of Madhyamgram, on the northern fringes of the city.																																																		Calcutta Municipal Corporation will celebrate February 21 as Matribhasha Diwas. A proposal in this regard was passed on Wednesday. A committee with representatives of all parties will be formed.																																																		Mayor Subrata Mukherjee will leave for Manila on January 24 to take part in a meeting at the Asian Development Bank head office and to check the water supply system of the city. Mayor-in-council (water supply), Shovan Chatterjee will accompany him.							TO lions club of calcutta sanjeevani and shradha eye care for organising a free eye-operation camp at New Alipore
